.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This module contains functions and symbols common to the
App::githook_perltidy::* modules.
.SH "EXPORTS"
.IX Header "EXPORTS"
The following functions and symbol are exported on request.
.IP "get_perltidyrc \-> Path::Tiny" 4
.IX Item "get_perltidyrc -> Path::Tiny"
Returns the location of a \f(CW\*(C`.perltidyrc\*(C'\fR file. Raises an exception when
the file is not found or if the file is not committed to the git
repository.
.IP "have_podtidy_opts \-> Boolean" 4
.IX Item "have_podtidy_opts -> Boolean"
Indicates the existence of a \f(CW\*(C`.podtidy\-opts\*(C'\fR file.
.IP "get_podtidy_opts \-> Path::Tiny" 4
.IX Item "get_podtidy_opts -> Path::Tiny"
Returns the location of a \f(CW\*(C`.podtidy\-opts\*(C'\fR file. Raises an exception
when the file is not found or if the file is not committed to the git
repository.
.ie n .IP "sys( @cmd ) \-> Str" 4
.el .IP "sys( \f(CW@cmd\fR ) \-> Str" 4
.IX Item "sys( @cmd ) -> Str"
Runs \f(CW@cmd\fR using the Perl \f(CW\*(C`system\*(C'\fR builtin. Raises an exception on
error.
.IP "\s-1POST_HOOK_FILE\s0" 4
.IX Item "POST_HOOK_FILE"
A constant value containing the name of the file for sharing
information between pre and post hook calls.
